Sub-policy 11
https://www.iubenda.com/privacy-policy/94654098:
Personal Data processed for the following purposes and using the following services:
Hosting and backend infrastructure
Amazon Web Services (AWS)
Personal Data: various types of Data as specified in the privacy policy of the service
MongoDB Cloud
Personal Data: Usage Data
Further information about the processing of Personal Data
Description of the service
The Consent Database makes it possible to keep track of Users’ consent activities and to store the information necessary to record evidence of that consent.
The tool consists of an API and a JavaScript library optimized for this purpose. The JavaScript library can be integrated into sites. Alternatively, it may be accessed by API via HTTPS.
For each User, the Consent Database allows obtaining the last preferences expressed, proof of their consent, and their full consent history.
When the Newsletter Opt-in Booster is activated, the email address and consent preferences will be transmitted to the Consent Database.
iubenda may process Personal Data related to Users if they are shared by the client with the Consent Database. In this case, it will be the client's duty to specify the nature of the Personal Data processed, within their privacy policy. When using iubenda's JavaScript library, the Personal Data processed are as follows: IP address.
Personal Data retention time
iubenda will retain Personal Data collected from the Client for the entire duration of the contract and an additional period of six months after the provision of the services has been completed, solely for the purpose of allowing the Controller to export it. Nevertheless, iubenda may retain Personal Data for a longer period if required by law.
After the expiration of the retention period, iubenda will delete all Personal Data.
Appointment of iubenda as Processor
Clients acknowledge and accept that by using the Consent Database they are engaging iubenda to process Personal Data as “processor” pursuant to and as defined under the Applicable Data Protection Laws. The terms of the engagement are outlined in the the
Data Processing Agreement
.
Such an agreement, the conclusion of which is required by law, therefore forms an integral and binding part of the contractual relationship between iubenda and its clients.
Appointment of iubenda as Service Provider
Clients acknowledge and accept that by using the Consent Database they are engaging iubenda to process Personal Data as "processor" pursuant to and as defined under the applicable US Privacy Laws . The terms of the engagement are outlined in the
US Data Processing Addendum
.
Such an agreement, the conclusion of which is required by law, therefore forms an integral and binding part of the contractual relationship between iubenda and its clients.
